title: About
text:
Aloha, I’m McKenzie Kananioaloha Tim Sing.
Hilo → Nāwahī → Chaminade.
I’m into mālama ʻāina, native ecosystems, and simple tools that help community learning.
This site is just a clean starter for class:
Home, Projects, About, one photo, and a tiny style tweak.

title: Lonoikamakahiki
text:
Hauʻoli Makahiki Hou!
The rising of Makaliʻi at sunset marks Makahiki, a season under Lono focused on peace, harvest, games, and community.
It usually runs mid-November through late January/February with the rainy season.
Makahiki traditions include hoʻokupu (offerings), ʻauhau (tribute), and games like heihei kūkini, mokomoko, hākōkō, pūhenehene, and kōnane.
It’s also a time to rest the land and strengthen relationships.
Learn more:
Makahiki: An Overview (KS Kaiwakīloumoku)

title: Aloha, I am McKenzie Kananioaloha Tim Sing
text:
“He kā, he iwi, he mākau, he lupe, ua lako ka ipu a ka hoʻokele”
ʻO Dale Codero ke kāne, ʻo Kassy Nohea Astrande ka wahine. Noho pū lāua a hānau ʻia ʻo McKenzie Kananioaloha Tim Sing ma Hilo i ka ua Kanilehua. He kama na ka Pūnana a puka aku mai ke Kula ʻo Nāwahīokalaniʻōpuʻu. He haumāna ʻimi i ke kekelē Laepua ENV Studies ma ke kulanui ʻo Kaminaka ma Oʻahu.
